OL,3,CMartyn's Law overcomes final hurdle in
OL,4,CParliament
OL,6,FOfficially titled the Terrorism
OL,7,F(Protection of Premises) Bill, it will
OL,8,Fcompel all UK venues that expect 200
OL,9,For more people to be on site to
OL,10,Fprepare for the event of a terror
OL,11,Fattack, such as establishing
OL,12,Fevacuation plans.
OL,14,FLarger premises expected to host 800
OL,15,Fpeople or more would also have to take
OL,16,Fsteps to reduce their vulnerability to
OL,17,Fan assault.
