OL,3,CMartyn's Law overcomes final hurdle in
OL,4,CParliament
OL,6,FHome Office minister Dan Jarvis
OL,7,Faccepted all of the amendments tabled
OL,8,Fby peers in the upper chamber and said
OL,9,Fthey would provide "further
OL,10,Fsafeguards".
OL,12,FMr Jarvis paid tribute to Ms Murray,
OL,13,Fwho watched on from the Commons'
OL,14,Fpublic gallery. He said: "Her campaign
OL,15,Fhas been nothing short of
OL,16,Fextraordinary.
